    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/11135½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: After our conversation
                    yesterday I prepared for your consideration the enclosed draft of a public
                    declaration in regard to the Czecho-Slovaks.<note n="2" xml:id="d103fn1">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I find there is a disposition among the newspapermen to discuss—possibly to
                    criticize—our silence in regard to this matter. I have been fortunate enough to
                    be able to stop it thus far but to tell the truth it is getting out of hand. I
                    hope therefore that we can do something very shortly.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
